# Database migrations (Alembic)

## Who does what (do not mix this up)

- **Agent / automated work:** Update **SQLAlchemy schema** under **`src/database/postgres/schema/`** (and aligned code: repos, models). Also update **`postgres_migrations/env.py`**: **import each new schema module** so the ORM class is loaded and registers on **`postgres_metadata`** (`target_metadata` for Alembic). **Do not** create, add, or edit **any** file under **`postgres_migrations/versions/`** — not even for a new phase or feature; the human is the only one who adds revisions (see below).
- **Human (you):** **Create and own migrations manually** — run **`./scripts/create_postgres_migration.sh "description"`**, then **hand-write** `upgrade` / `downgrade` in the generated revision, then apply with **`./scripts/run_postgres_migration.sh`** (`head`, `+1`, `-1` per script help). Do not document raw `alembic` CLI as the default workflow in repo docs.

This avoids repeating the mistake of committing migration revisions from agent sessions while the team keeps sole ownership of DDL timing and review.

## Policy

- **Write migration revision files manually** (explicit `upgrade` / `downgrade`).
- **Do not** treat **autogenerate-from-ORM** as the default source of truth for committed revisions unless the team explicitly adopted that workflow. Prefer **reviewed, intentional DDL**.

## Migration file ownership

- **`postgres_migrations/env.py`** is part of **schema registration** (import side effects on `postgres_metadata`); update it when adding tables, same as **`schema/`** — still **no** committed autogen revisions as truth.
- **Do not** add or edit files under **`postgres_migrations/versions/`** as drive-by or **agent** work unless the repo explicitly allows it.
- New revisions start from **`./scripts/create_postgres_migration.sh`**; the **human** edits the generated revision file, then runs **`./scripts/run_postgres_migration.sh`**.
- When schema or indexes are needed and an agent is implementing features, the agent updates **`src/database/postgres/schema/`** and **`postgres_migrations/env.py`** (imports); if helpful, **describe** the required DDL in PR text, comments, or chat so the owner can produce the matching migration file under **`versions/`**.

## Practice

- Name revisions clearly; keep **`upgrade`** and **`downgrade`** symmetric and safe for shared environments.
- Coordinate **`src/database/postgres/schema/`**, **`postgres_migrations/env.py`**, and the **human-written** revision under **`versions/`** so ORM metadata and database stay aligned—still **no** autogen as the source of truth for the file content unless policy says otherwise.

